<section>
  <h2>Accessibility</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Tier 1 button has <code>aria-label="Share this page"</code></li>
    <li>Tier 2 wraps buttons in <code>&lt;nav aria-label="Share this page"&gt;</code></li>
    <li>Each platform button has an accessible label: "Share on X", "Copy link", etc.</li>
    <li>Copy button announces "Copied!" via <code>aria-live="polite"</code></li>
    <li>Icons are hidden from assistive technology with <code>aria-hidden="true"</code></li>
    <li>Labels remain in the DOM for <code>icon</code> variant (visually hidden, not removed)</li>
    <li>Reduced motion: transitions disabled via <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code></li>
  </ul>
</section>
